data.chText: 有价值的人（或事物）；有用的人（或事物）
data.enText: a person or thing that is valuable or useful to sb/sth
She'll be an asset to the team.

data.chText: 他干的这份工作，耐心是无价之宝。
data.enText: In his job, patience is an invaluable asset.
a thing of value, especially property, that a person or company owns, which can be used or sold to pay debts
the net asset value of the company

data.chText: 她的财产包括公司的股份和在法国的一座房子。
data.enText: Her assets include shares in the company and a house in France.

ex.chText: 我们是一家中美合资企业，注册资本为1亿美元。
ex.enText: We are a Sino-US joint venture with a registered capital of USD 100 million.

ex.chText: 他们向该企业投入了大量资金。
ex.enText: They invested huge capital in the enterprise.

synonyms.bx: 指创办企业所需的启动资金。

ex.chText: 她的资产全部被冻结了。

ex.enText: He has an excess of assets over liabilities.

synonyms.bx: 指个人、企业等拥有的可以抵债的资产，通常用复数。

ex.chText: 如果不能得到更多的资金，我们将只得关闭这家工厂。
ex.enText: Unless we can get more finance, we'll have to close the factory.

ex.chText: 他需要为进一步研究筹资。
ex.enText: He needs to raise finance for further research.

synonyms.bx: 指由银行或其他机构提供的用以资助某项事业的资金。

ex.chText: 这笔花费已使我们的资金所剩无几。
ex.enText: This expense has depleted our funds.

synonyms.bx: 指某一机构、企业等需要或拥有的资金。

ex.enText: I have to take out a loan to buy a house.

ex.chText: 他将债券作抵押以取得贷款。
ex.enText: He used bonds as collateral for a loan.

synonyms.bx: 指从银行等机构借来的钱款。

value.def: Something or someone that is an asset is considered useful or helps a person or organization to be successful.

example.ex: Her leadership qualities were the greatest asset of the Conservative Party...
example.tran: 她的领导才能是保守党最宝贵的财富。

example.ex: His Republican credentials made him an asset.
example.tran: 他作为共和党人的资历成了他的一笔财富。

value.def: The assets of a company or a person are all the things that they own.

example.ex: By the end of 1989 the group had assets of 3.5 billion francs.
example.tran: 到1989年底该集团拥有的资产达35亿法郎。
